channel.title: Need Help Setting My Enviormental Variables Set Right
channel.description:
Hey. I'm trying to start my own Runescape Private server and everything was running fine, until my Compiler didn't work. So I went to change my Enviormental Variables, because I read that, if I did, it would run compiler properly, but instead of fixing the compiler. It didn't only not fix the Compiler, it made it so that when I go to "run server" a Command Prompt flashes over and over saying 'cannont find path specified'
Here are my current variables for 'Path' : path-C:\Program Files\Java\jdk7.0.0_0\bin;
*Note* Yes I know it says JDK7, but it was set to like 6.1.0_26. It was set to the most current java, I changed it trying to fix it.
Please Contact me by replying to this post or contacting me on skype(preferred).
Skype:joshua.anderson5
I am running a 32-bit computer for any wondering..
